        <div class="text">
          <p>Sometimes success depends on fortune, the story of the first browser with graphic interface Erwise illustrates it perfectly. Perhaps you have never heard about it.</p>
          <p>Erwise had to become an popularizer of Web, it had ambitions. However everything went not as planned.</p>
          <h1>The developers of Erwice are insightful persons.</h1>
          <p>Niche was absolutely new. The Internet have been just developed by Tim Bernerce-Li in ZERN. His colleagues and him, essentially Robert Kayo, were engaging by spreading the information about the Internet and inventing standards for it. Though there were created some browsers, there were lack of simplicity in usage.</p>
          <p>Bernerce-Li knew that the Internet needs a browser based on graphic interface, that one that could work on several operating system, what is more, it must be convenient PCs were new that time too!</p>
          <p>As long as Bernerce-Li and his colleagues hadn’t create new browser they persuaded others to do that. With understanding that development of browsers could be a perfect niche for project they started visiting European Uviversities.</p>
          <p>In 1991 Robert Kayo visited technologic University of Helsinki. Four young enthusiastic master students were very impressed by meeting with him and decided to develop a browser for a dissertation.</p>
          <p>Kim Nighberg, Teemu Rantanen, Katy Suominen and Kary
Sydyanmalakka started to work under the guidance of Ari Lemmke. The anticipated this “Big Deal”.</p>
        </div>

